<p>
<seg id=1> The International Court of Justice, which sits at The Hague, pronounced 3 defendants guilty of war crimes towards the Serbs of Bosnia, but their commander was pronounced not guilty. </seg>
<seg id=2> According to the ruling of the International Court, Bosnian Moslem Ed Vulliamy could not be responsible for his subordinate's crime towards the Serbian prisoners of war at Camp Omarsk in 1992. </seg>
<seg id=3> The other 3 defendants were pronounced specified sentences because of their roles in the reign of terror in the camp as told by the prisoners of war. </seg>
</p>
